<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
This species was previously recorded only for the Amazon rainforest (Northern region of Brazil) and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, APM" journalOrPublisher="PeerJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" publicationUrl="http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" refId="B68" refString="Santos, APM, Dumas, LL, Henriques-Oliveira, AL, Souza, WRM, Camargos, LM, Calor, AR, Pes, AMO, 2022. Trichoptera in Catalogo Taxonomico da Fauna do Brasil. PNUD. http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" title="Trichoptera in Catalogo Taxonomico da Fauna do Brasil. PNUD." url="http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" year="2022">Santos et al. 2022</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3700.4.6" author="Souza, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="583 - 587" refId="B77" refString="Souza, WRM, Santos, APM, Lima, LRC, Pinheiro, U, 2013b. A new species and new records of microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) from northeastern Brazil. Zootaxa 3700 (4): 583 - 587, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3700.4.6" title="A new species and new records of microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) from northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3700.4.6" volume="3700" year="2013 b">Souza et al. (2013b)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it for the Caatinga, Northeast Brazil. This study reports this species for the first time in Atlantic Forest (Brejo de Altitude).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
